---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Guest Artist Lecture — Marty Beller">
	<!-- Hero -->
	<section class="relative flex flex-col justify-between overflow-hidden bg-cover bg-center px-12 pb-28" style="background-image: url('/mb-lecture-bg-v1.webp')">
		<div></div>
		<h1 class="font-headline text-[120px] font-light leading-[0.83] text-white">GUEST ARTIST<br />LECTURE.</h1>
	</section>

	<!-- Intro -->
	<section class="px-12 pt-24">
		<div class="mx-auto flex max-w-[var(--container-max)] gap-12">
			<!-- Left column -->
			<div class="flex w-1/2 flex-col justify-between gap-12">
				<h2 class="font-body text-[45px] font-medium leading-[1.17] text-white">Twists, Turns and Breakthroughs: Inside the Work of a Recording, Touring &amp; Composing Career</h2>
				<p class="font-body text-[32px] font-normal leading-tight text-white">Marty Beller, Grammy Award–winning composer and longtime drummer for the iconic alt-rock band They Might Be Giants, brings students inside the real world of a professional musician whose career moves seamlessly between recording, touring, and scoring for the screen—on stage, in the studio, and in the creative spaces where projects come to life.</p>
			</div>
			<!-- Right column -->
			<div class="flex w-1/2 flex-col gap-10">
				<p class="font-body text-[32px] font-normal leading-tight text-neutral-400">This 90-120 minute interactive lecture is designed for university music students and is ideal for lecture series, visiting artist programs, and music school forums.</p>
				<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-white">Drawing on decades of experience drumming with They Might Be Giants and scoring for Film/TV, Marty brings students into the recording studio, onto the stage, and into vibrant creative meetings, immersing them in a whirlwind of twists, turns, and breakthroughs. Do you want this all-consuming, exhilarating lifestyle more than anything else in the world?! Yes, you do!</p>
				<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-white">Students leave with a clear understanding of what a working music career looks like — and a real picture of what comes next. They will have learned about real workflow, taking direction, digesting feedback, and making creative decisions, whether recording, touring, or scoring. Most importantly, students will be inspired to develop their own unique voice as musicians and collaborators.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Testimonial -->
	<section class="px-12 pt-24">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--container-max)] overflow-hidden rounded-xl bg-white/25 p-6">
			<blockquote class="flex flex-col gap-4">
				<p class="max-w-[867px] font-accent text-2xl font-medium leading-snug text-white">"Marty showed our students that a career in music can take many shapes and inspired them to pursue their own creative vision."</p>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-6">
					<div class="h-[72px] w-[72px] shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-neutral-500"></div>
					<p class="font-accent text-base font-medium leading-tight text-white">Colton Dodd<br />Professor at Peabody Institute at Johns Hopkins University</p>
				</div>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- The Rundown -->
	<section class="px-12 pt-24">
		<div class="mx-auto flex max-w-[var(--container-max)] flex-col gap-6">
			<h2 class="font-accent text-5xl font-medium leading-snug text-white">The Rundown</h2>
			<div class="flex gap-12">
				<!-- Left column: items 1–4 -->
				<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-10 pb-8">
					<!-- Item 1 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">1</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] leading-none font-medium text-white">Let It Fly</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">Put Your Personality Into Your Music</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">The moment I realized that individuality is your greatest asset.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<hr class="border-white/50" />
					<!-- Item 2 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">2</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">The Big Break</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">My First Show with They Might Be Giants</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">How I got the gig, made the most of it, and what I learned along the way.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<hr class="border-white/50" />
					<!-- Item 3 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">3</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">Composing</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">From the initial call to the final mix</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">How to approach key creative meetings, turn adjectives and emotions into music, and deliver on the client's vision.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<hr class="border-white/50" />
					<!-- Item 4 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">4</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">You Got The Job</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">Time for your first creative meeting</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">Students take on the roles of composer and showrunner, guided by Marty. Stranger Things is the &ldquo;show&rdquo; for this roleplay.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<!-- Right column: items 5–7 -->
				<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-10">
					<!-- Item 5 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">5</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">In the Studio</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">Recording with They Might Be Giants</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">Take direction, process feedback, trial and error. Be ready to pivot. Be inventive and musical. Make your part immediate. Serve the song.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<hr class="border-white/50" />
					<!-- Item 6 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">6</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">The Million Dollar Question</h3>
							<p class="font-accent text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-white">How do you get gigs?</p>
							<p class="font-body text-2xl font-normal leading-snug text-neutral-400">There is no formula, I wish there was, but these ideas have worked for me (I've got the stories to prove it).</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<hr class="border-white/50" />
					<!-- Item 7 -->
					<div class="flex gap-7">
						<span class="font-headline text-[40px] font-light leading-none tracking-[2px] text-neutral-500">7</span>
						<div class="flex flex-1 flex-col gap-6">
							<h3 class="font-headline text-[32px] font-medium text-white">Q&amp;A. I Love Q&amp;A!</h3>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Beyond the Lecture -->
	<section class="px-12 pt-24">
		<div class="mx-auto flex max-w-[var(--container-max)] flex-col gap-10">
			<h2 class="font-accent text-5xl font-medium leading-snug text-white">Beyond the Lecture</h2>
			<p class="font-body text-[32px] font-normal leading-tight text-neutral-400">Marty would be genuinely excited to extend his time on campus and has designed his lecture to be flexible and adaptive. Here are some examples: Extended/Expanded Lectures, One-on-One Coaching/Mentoring, and Ensemble/Studio visits.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
